Package: tcptraceroute
Version: 1.2
Revision: 3
Maintainer: Jeremy Higgs <jhiggs@iprsystems.com>
Depends: libnet, libpcap-shlibs
BuildDepends: libpcap
Source: http://michael.toren.net/code/%n/%n-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: e31e3f5bfd817d32ed6d954382ca768d
CompileScript: <<
 echo "No configure script."
 (cc -Wall -I%p/include -I/usr/include -no-cpp-precomp `libnet-config --defines` -o tcptraceroute tcptraceroute.c `libnet-config --libs` -L%p/lib -lpcap)
<<
InstallScript: <<
 mkdir -p %i/bin
 mkdir -p %i/share/man/man8
 mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n
 install -m 755 tcptraceroute %i/bin
 install -m 644 tcptraceroute.8 %i/share/man/man8
 install -m 644 tcptraceroute.8.html COPYING README %i/share/doc/%n
<<
Description: Alternative to traceroute, using TCP packets
DescDetail: <<
tcptraceroute is an alternative to traditional traceroute, which uses TCP 
packets that are generally able to traverse firewall filters.
<<
Homepage: http://michael.toren.net/code/tcptraceroute/
